Ralph W. TAYLOR v. UNITED STATES DISTRICT COURT, DISTRICT OF KANSAS, Topeka, Kansas. No. 7112. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. Sept. 14, 1962. No representation for petitioner. Newell A. George, U. S. Atty., and Benjamin E. Franklin, Asst. U. S. Atty., Topeka, Kan., for respondent.

Before MURRAH, Chief Judge, and PICKETT, Circuit Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Motion for writ of mandamus denied September 14, 1962.
